<TITLE> HC rules on Justice Wahab's appointment </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 8 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court has asked the government to explain why Justice Abdul Wahab did not get appointed as a permanent judge despite recommendations from the chief justice and why the decision is not illegal. The bench of justices Nazmun Ara Sultana and Mohammad Rezaul Haque issued the rule Sunday upon a writ petition filed by Justice Wahab 23 years after he was deprived of the job. Justice Wahab was appointed as a temporary judge to the High Court on May 29, 1984. Two years later, his two other colleagues, who were given appointment temporarily, were elevated to the High Court as permanent judges. Wahab petitioned the High Court on Feb. 15. His lawyer Amir-Ul Islam said in the hearing on the petition that Justice Wahab entered the age of 67, the retirement age for judges, on May 30, 2001. All he wants now is the recognition of a permanent judge, not facilities, the lawyer told the court. b
